‚úÖ How to Run the Project by Cloning from GitHub

If someone already uploaded the Experiment-12 code to GitHub, then you don‚Äôt need to create files manually.
You can simply clone the repository and run the project.

Here is how:

‚úî STEP 1 ‚Äî Clone the Git Repository

Run this in PowerShell:

git clone https://github.com/Srivaishnavi08/tests 


Example:

git clone https://github.com/koushik9848/exp12-selenium.git

‚úî STEP 2 ‚Äî Go Inside the Project
cd exp12-selenium


You should now see these files:

Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
index.html
seleniumTest.py

‚úî STEP 3 ‚Äî Start Docker Services

Make sure Docker Desktop is running.

Then run:

docker compose up --build


‚ö†Ô∏è Important:
Use hyphen (-) not en-dash (‚Äì).

‚úî Correct:

docker compose up --build


‚ùå Wrong:

docker compose ‚Äìf up --build


This will:

Start the HTML App (http://localhost:8000
)

Start Selenium Chrome (http://localhost:4444
)

‚úî STEP 4 ‚Äî Run the Selenium Test Script

Open another terminal window:

python seleniumTest.py


You will see:

Browser actions in Selenium Grid

Login attempt

Dashboard page OR error message

Video recording

Console output:

Login Successful!

OR Login failed: Incorrect credentials

‚úî STEP 5 ‚Äî Stop Services

When done:

docker compose down



