üìÅ Folder Structure (Create Manually)
exp12/
‚îÇ‚îÄ‚îÄ index.html
‚îÇ‚îÄ‚îÄ Dockerfile
‚îÇ‚îÄ‚îÄ docker-compose.yml
‚îÇ‚îÄ‚îÄ seleniumTest.py

üìå 1. index.html (FULL CODE)

Create a file named index.html and paste this:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Simple Login App</title>
<style>
    body {
        font-family: Arial;
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 50px;
    }
    #dashboard {
        display: none;
    }
    #error-message {
        color: red;
        display: none;
    }
</style>
</head>

<body>

<h1>Welcome to the Application</h1>

<a href="#" id="get-started">Get started</a>

<div id="login-section" style="display:none;">
    <h2>Login</h2>
    <input id="user_email_login" type="text" placeholder="Enter email"><br><br>
    <input id="user_password" type="password" placeholder="Enter password"><br><br>
    <button name="commit" id="login-btn">Login</button>

    <p id="error-message">Invalid username or password!</p>
</div>

<div id="dashboard">
    <h2>Dashboard</h2>
    <p>Login successful! Welcome to your dashboard.</p>
</div>

<script>
document.getElementById("get-started").addEventListener("click", function() {
    document.getElementById("login-section").style.display = "block";
});

document.getElementById("login-btn").addEventListener("click", function() {
    let email = document.getElementById("user_email_login").value;
    let pass = document.getElementById("user_password").value;

    if(email === "abc@gmail.com" && pass === "password") {
        document.getElementById("dashboard").style.display = "block";
        document.getElementById("error-message").style.display = "none";
    } else {
        document.getElementById("error-message").style.display = "block";
        document.getElementById("dashboard").style.display = "none";
    }
});
</script>

</body>
</html>

üìå 2. Dockerfile (FULL CODE)

Create a file named Dockerfile:

FROM python:3.9
WORKDIR /app
COPY index.html .
EXPOSE 8000
CMD ["python", "-m", "http.server", "8000"]

üìå 3. docker-compose.yml (FULL CODE)

Create a file named docker-compose.yml:

services:
  app:
    build:
      context: .
      dockerfile: Dockerfile
    container_name: html-server
    ports:
      - "8000:8000"

  selenium:
    image: selenium/standalone-chrome
    container_name: selenium-chrome
    ports:
      - "4444:4444"
    depends_on:
      - app

üìå 4. seleniumTest.py (FULL CODE)

Create a file named seleniumTest.py:

from selenium import webdriver
from selenium.webdriver.common.by import By
from selenium.webdriver.support.ui import WebDriverWait
from selenium.webdriver.support import expected_conditions as EC
import time

print("Test Execution Started")

options = webdriver.ChromeOptions()
options.add_argument('--ignore-ssl-errors=yes')
options.add_argument('--ignore-certificate-errors')

driver = webdriver.Remote(
    command_executor='http://localhost:4444/wd/hub',
    options=options
)

driver.maximize_window()
time.sleep(10)

driver.get("http://host.docker.internal:8000")
time.sleep(10)

try:
    link = WebDriverWait(driver, 30).until(
        EC.element_to_be_clickable((By.ID, "get-started"))
    )
    link.click()
    time.sleep(5)

    WebDriverWait(driver, 10).until(EC.presence_of_element_located((By.ID, "user_email_login")))
    WebDriverWait(driver, 10).until(EC.presence_of_element_located((By.ID, "user_password")))

    username = driver.find_element(By.ID, "user_email_login")
    password = driver.find_element(By.ID, "user_password")
    login_button = driver.find_element(By.ID, "login-btn")

    username.send_keys("abc@gmail.com")
    password.send_keys("password")
    login_button.click()

    try:
        WebDriverWait(driver, 10).until(
            EC.visibility_of_element_located((By.ID, "dashboard"))
        )
        print("Login Successful!")
    except:
        print("Login failed: Incorrect credentials")

except Exception as e:
    print("Error:", e)

finally:
    time.sleep(5)
    driver.quit()
    print("Test Execution Completed!")

‚úÖ HOW TO RUN THE FULL PROJECT
‚úî Step 1 ‚Äî Build & Start Containers
docker compose up --build

‚úî Step 2 ‚Äî Run Selenium Test

Open another terminal:

python seleniumTest.py

‚úî Step 3 ‚Äî Stop Everything
docker compose dow
